# SDLC And Artifact Rules

This repository enforces the strict enterprise SDLC defined in root `CLAUDE.md`.

- Never skip a phase; never jump directly to implementation.
- No implementation before phases `00` through `13` are documented.
- Depth may scale with request size, but phase existence and hard gates never disappear.
- Every request writes or updates artifacts (`00-intake.md` … `27-retrospective.md`) under
  `docs/features/<feature-slug>/`.
- Tests and docs ship in the same delivery stream as the behavior they cover.
- Every release-facing change must be reviewed, tested, documented, observable, and reversible.

Locations:

- `docs/sdlc/` — permanent company baselines
- `docs/features/<feature-slug>/` — request-specific phase artifacts
- `test-cases/` — detailed reusable test cases
- `architecture/adrs/` — architecture decisions
- `runbooks/` — operational procedures
- `release-notes/` — release communication
- `support/` — support-facing guidance

Do not merge or release when any of the following is true: required artifacts missing; tests for
changed behavior missing; docs stale; touched-module coverage below threshold without waiver;
lint / typecheck / test / build / security gates failing; architecture impact undocumented;
rollback undefined; observability undefined for material risk; required QA / security / business
approvals missing.
